post_text:
On Friday, May 15, 2020, Yorktown Independent School District will be having an End of the School Year Teacher Parade. This will give teachers and students a way of saying good-bye to each other for the 2019-20 school year. The district‚Äôs teachers will drive their cars or ride on flat bed trailers, as the parade winds its way along the school‚Äôs in-town bus routes. Students are encouraged to make signs for their teachers to show their support. Social distancing will be maintained at all times. Teachers will not leave their vehicles and students will not be allowed to approach any vehicle in the parade. Parents who have students who live out of town are encouraged to park their vehicle with their children in the parking lot between the Admin Building and the Bus Barn to watch the parade. There are also a few natural viewing spots on the route at the Methodist Church parking lot and the backside of the city park. The parade will be begin at 11am and end between 12:30pm and
1:00pm.

post_text:
Mr. Larry Barnett, a retired band director from Goliad ISD will serve as a part-time interim band director for YISD. He will teach the 7th, 8th, and high school band classes as well as attend football games and band practices. With Mr. Barnett serving as interim, the Wildcat band can continue moving forward while YISD takes the time and care needed to find the right band director to lead our amazing students.

Mr. Barnett will begin work Monday. We will have a student/parent meeting at 5:00 p.m. on Monday and then he will have his first practice with the band after the meeting.

Thank you for your continued support.

Yesterday the Wildcat Band held Drum Major tryouts and we are very proud to announce that Aubriana Longoria was selected to be your new Drum Major for the Wildcat Band. We are very excited to see the great things she does while leading the Wildcat Band.

When asked about her goals for the upcoming season she stated "I would like to lead the band and get us to Straight 1s in marching. My motto for this year is going to be New Goals/Same Mindset."

Thank each of you for your support and please congratulate Aubriana if you see her throughout the day. The future is bright for our program.

THIS IS OUR TIME!

Musically Yours,
Trent Enriquez
Yorktown ISD Director of Bands

This week we have two great opportunities to support our students in the fine arts!

Monday, March 4th - the Wildcat Band Band will be performing their UIL concert pieces at 3:00p.m. in the auditorium. Additionally, they will be traveling to Canyon Lake HS on Wednesday to compete at the UIL Concert and Sight-Reading contest. Also Monday, the UIL One Act Play group will perform at 6:00p.m. in the Auditorium for parents and the community. They will perform on Friday at 9:30a.m. for students.

post_text: The Yorktown Independent School District school board unanimously voted to make Katherine Kuenstler the lone finalist in the superintendent search for YISD. Mrs. Kuenstler is currently serving as the assistant superintendent of curriculum and instruction for Comfort ISD. Kuenstler has also been a counselor and served for seven years as Comfort's high school principal. Prior to her experience in Comfort, Mrs. Kuenstler was a math teacher for eight years in Linden-Kildare CISD. She has served Comfort ISD for 15 years. Mrs Kuenstler is married and has four kids, two of which will be a part of YISD. When contacted about being the lone finalist, Mrs. Kuenstler said, " I am honored and proud to be lone finalist of Yorktown ISD. I'm eager to listen, and learn from the stakeholders to continue to provide the best education for our students. Together, we we will make a difference". Start date for Ms. Kuenstler is projected for March 18th.

post_text:
Operation Save February/Don't let the Blood Bus Leave

Yorktown High School is hosting the Greatest Blood Drive EVER!!!!!

Where: Yorktown High School parking lot

When: Wednesday, February 28th from 8am-12pm (if donors show up the bus will stay......hints the Don't let the Blood Bus leave theme)

We need every persons help to make this goal of 31 units. We currently have 21 sign ups and need about 20 more to show up to make our goal (Not everybody is always an eligible donor, but stop and try out. At the very least you'll get a mini physical)

The Flu-season has put a huge strain on the blood industry, but we still have a responsibility to help our patients in need. Please tell your friends and family about this awesome chance to change a persons life.
As always walk-in are welcome(may have a small wait time) and thank you for rolling up your sleeve and being a true life saver!

post_text:
YHS Project Graduation 2018 is teaming up with the wonderful folks at Warrior's Weekend and offering US Flag Sponsorships for $40 to honor a Veteran, encourage a Warrior or show your patriotism by sponsoring a flag.

The flags are 3'x5' and will be flown on an 8' staff with a label affixed with the name of the person or family you are honoring. The Field of Honor will consist of perfect rows and columns of flags located at Parkway Church, 4802 John Stockbauer, in Victoria, from May 5th through the 28th. Flags will be placed on May 5th between 9 am and 1 pm, and sponsors are welcome to be there to place their flag, but it isn't necessary. When the tribute is complete, flags may be picked up on May 29th or 30th between 5 & 7 pm, or you may choose to donate your flag to Warrior's Weekend. If interested, please contact a YHS Senior Class Member. Deadline for Project Graduation to sell sponsorships is Friday, March 9th.

The baseball program will be having a work day on January 20 from 9-3. Anyone playing baseball this season needs to attend for however long their schedule will allow, local community members may help if they choose to. Coach Dunnam and his family will provide lunch for those who attend.

Here is a list of things that we will be working on:
Repairing and cleaning the batting cage
Infield and outfield dirt work
Putting together the new rolling cage
Painting poles and dugouts

Thank you in advance for helping our Wildcat baseball program and we look forward to seeing everyone at the ballpark this spring.

post_text: Our Veteran's Day Ceremony will start promptly at 9:00 tomorrow morning. We would like to encourage you to attend and help our students honor our veterans. Parents we are asking that elementary students try to wear red, junior high students wear white, and high school students wear blue.

post_text: Your Yorktown Kitty Kats will face Freer Saturday in the Area Round of the volleyball playoffs. The game will be in George West at 3:00 pm in their gym. Come out and show your support for these young ladies as they compete to move on in the playoffs. Go Kats, beat Freer!

post_text: Great day at YES as we welcomed representatives from GVEC as they presented a check to Mrs. Carriger and the ABC to help purchase more technology for our students. The grant will be used to purchase IPADs and Tablets for students to use in conjunction with our Yorktown Literacy Initiative. We would like to extend our gratitude to GVEC for their generocity and Mrs. Carriger for her hard work in securing this award.
